</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirlageholyblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Lage Holyblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/3/02 6:36:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15416.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: no we're not and any of you who say we are are fools!</span><hr size=1> &quot;Or the other way of looking at that is &quot;which classes by design from just turning on autoattack are going to be the people the ubermob turns on and trys to squash?&quot; That's right, its the folks that are designed to be doing warrior or warrior+ damage and constantly working to manage their agro. (with bard as the odd man out, and I don't know enough about bst + pet at 60). Hmmm, DA would be, oh, several hundred times more useful to a monk than just voiddance itself is, so maybe that's a bias in my view... &quot;<br>
<br>
I'm not sure I understand your point here.  I agree that DA would be more useful to a monk in the given situation, but in theory they won't want the aggro.  We're supposed to get it, but as it stands now, we'd get squashed faster then the monk.  &lt;shrug&gt;<br>
<br>
&quot;Personally I am against changes/improvement to classes that take the zest out of high end encounters or destroy the role of other classes. (This is a general statement not necessarily to the discussion about getting paladins a 18sec mitigation disc)&quot;<br>
<br>
I agree.  However, a ~10 second avoidance disc will not destroy anyones roll.  Warriors will stil be the main and preferred uber mob tanks, but we would move up to a feasable second option.  Without the ability to 1) Hold aggro and 2) Stay alive for ~ 10 seconds, we can't do that.  Any  of the other mentioned classes can.<br>
<br>
I do disagree on a point though.  It does not take the 'zeal' out of encounters, what it does is create a semi viable option.  Why should the *whole* raid have to fail if the warrior dies?  That's too much power put into one class.  I think the game *needs* another, weaker, yet viable, option out there.<br>
<br>
&quot;Coming back to the discussion about a 18-20sec avoidance disc, I am personally against it since it would simplify many fights. In high end raids, the toughest and battle winning challenge is keeping aggro on one tank and keep him alive.&quot;<br>
<br>
Relying on one tank is not challenging.  It is simply the *only* strategy due to the lack of options, namely the fact that the supposed second best tank, lack *any* ability to stay alive vs a uber mob long enough to get a CHeal chain going.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here comes the difference between paladins and the classes that already have a 18-20 100% avoidance discs: We can gain aggro almost instantenously compared to the other classes. The same is true for SKs.&quot;<br>
<br>
In exp groups, yeah.  It's not that simple to get the aggro when the main tank drops vs a uber mob.  Either way, I don't see anything wrong with it remaining possible, yet less effecient/likely, to still be able to win the battle without the big bad warrior.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now lets give a paladins a 18-20 sec disc. MT dies and paladin in 5 seconds has fully aggro. Maybe 1-2 die till the paladin is up. With a avoidance disc the clerics would have 18-20 seconds to get the CH chain reestablished and the battle would easily be won. That is forever.&quot;<br>
<br>
No, it would not be easily won.  A paladin getting hit for 600 - 1k a pop is not an effecient tank.  You still want a warrior to get the aggro.  Both the warrior and Paladin *only* attack the mob for the 10 seconds that the Paladin is /disc'd avoidance, at the end of which, he DA's and the aggro will go back to the new warrior.  Then, you win.  It does not replace the warriors role.<br>
<br>
You realize, that it is probable, with our complacency, and the druids lack of, that they will become the new AoE healers.  Where is that going to leave you then?<br>
<br>
&quot;Currently when the MT dies unplanned, a bunch of folks die until a new tank can be successfully established. This makes the battles challenging and fun. That makes you proud when you can reestablish a new tank through the skill of everyone &quot;<br>
<br>
I guess.  It's not exactly my idea of fun.  Getting squished nearly as fast as a cloth wearing caster vs a uber mob was not what I had in mind for a plate wearing holy warrior.  Or, cowardly hitting DA to *ensure* that the cloth wearer gets smashed first.  Again, I have a different vision for a holy warrior, perhaps the ability to withstand 10 second sof punishment vs a uber mob like the other melees and hybrids?<br>
<br>
&quot;Even if you do not establish a CH chain, each paladin with def disc up will give the raid a free 18-20 second well aggro controlled time to finish a mob. Fights like Klandicar or Sont would become so boring since 5 pals with our uncanny ability to hold aggro could totally negate the need to even heal the MTs.&quot;<br>
<br>
That I will have to take your word on.  I find it hard to believe that it would work quite as well as you think it would.<br>
<br>
Oh, and I advocate a 10 second disc.  I'm not sure where the 18-20 sec came from.  That, I would agree, to be too powerful.<br>
